  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Soc. Accountability in the Utilisation Of Public Resources through Citizens&#x2019; Participation</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Capacity strengthening
&#x2022;Develop a Social Accountability Training Manual that contains a compendium of success stories of local governance and social accountability initiatives and telling the stories of distinguished Assembly members and public officers. 
Participatory Monitoring &amp; Tracking 
&#x2022;Validation Citizens&#x2019; report Card and monitoring report 
&#x2022;Dissemination of reports
Community mobilisation and outreach
&#x2022;Town Hall meetings to provide the platform for citizens to interact with Assembly officials and seek responses on their development challenges 
Documentation and innovative technology 
&#x2022;Develop a web-based &#x201C;Accountability TV&#x201D; to share financial information and utilisation of minerals royalties of the 4 Districts on quarterly basis. 
&#x2022;Develop and disseminate an SMS alert system to disseminate financial information to 4,000 people in the four Districts.
Video documentary to highlight the project results, challenges, lessons learnt and testimonies of beneficiaries</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improved responsiveness, transparency and accountability in local governance that translates to enhanced service delivery and reduced poverty.</narrative>
  </description>
